  "text": "Possible measure to improve the innovation performance of the agri-food system is the strengthening of interactions between agents in the system. Two kinds of interactions can be taken into account (Europe Innova, 2007) . One is to promote innovation through enhanced cooperation and exchange between firms. In particular, interactions with knowledge-intensive sectors, given their importance in the generation and diffusion of innovations, can be strengthened [CITATION_1] . In this empowerment of innovation networks, the innovation brokers may have a key role [CITATION_2] . The other is to enhance partnership between the business sector and public support services to R&D activities. Such kind of services play an es- 1 \"Other products\" has not been analyzed because is very heterogeneous and its ratio value added/production is so small that distorts the results.",
